      "comment": "KEEN ON KEV (1) had some strong recent form but was below best last time when eighth (19.87) in a Grade 5 at Healesville. Generally a safe beginner but buried in the ruck from a squeeze draw last time. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Has winning claims on his best figures. MEPUNGA INFRARED (2) comes off a big run when second in a solid 29.50 at Mt Gambier over 512m. Expecting another bold showing. ALLIGATOR ROCK (3) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 8th at Shepparton following on from a second place finish (24.07) at Bendigo the start prior. Can figure in the finish. OVER ACHIEVER (4) must be included in calculations.",
